          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "When the value of this property is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the speech recognizer’s commands are only recognized when the speech recognizer’s application is the frontmost application—typically the application displaying the menu bar. If the value of the property is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/no"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", the commands are recognized regardless of the visibility of the application, including agent applications (agent applications, which have the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "LSUIElement"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property set, do not appear in the Dock or Force Quit window). The default value of this property is "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/objectivec/yes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
